race.comment: SINHALESE (5) looks well placed here. He was a smart maiden winner first up at Yarra Valley, tackling a stronger race at Sandown Hillside last time over 1800m when just holding his ground. By Almanzor, he should appreciate getting over a trip for the first time and will take holding out. MACY MOON (1) wasn't far away here last start having gone close two back at Wodonga as well. He should roll forward here and looks to have found a nice race. DONEGAL SOUL (11) can mix her form but was good here last start when getting into third. She can track up from the low gate and figure in the finish. VELLASGLORY (12) won his maiden easily at Stony Creek last time when rising to 2100m. He's found his right range now and could take catching again.
